hopobject.body: Can you hear me OK? buy cialis online uk As the 2010 Tate exhibition demonstrated, he spent an enormous amount of time studying and emulating the art of the past: Claude, the Dutch master of the 17th century, Ruisdael and Titian. One of his wishes was to have two of his own paintings exhibited with the Claudes in the National Gallery. But his subsequent reputation has been that of a revolutionary: the precursor of the Impressionists and even Mark Rothko. He was, perhaps – in a characteristic English manner – at once a conservative and a radical.
